headline: A Look At Texas Instruments (TXN) Valuation As Analyst Upgrades Highlight Industrial Restocking Cycle
summary: Analyst upgrades and industrial restocking set the stage Texas Instruments (TXN) is back in focus after multiple analyst upgrades tied to a broad industrial restocking cycle and growing attention on its upcoming Q4 and full year 2025 earnings call. With industrial customers accounting for a meaningful share of revenue, investors are watching how restocking trends intersect with Texas Instruments' existing margin pressures and its recent share price gains over the past month and the past three...
